WEBVTT

00:04.129 --> 00:07.667
Our Twilight Zone acid trip
to the, uh, Phantom Prison...

00:07.841 --> 00:09.581
...that place was....

00:09.759 --> 00:11.624
-Kryptonian.
-Mm.

00:15.098 --> 00:19.011
And that horny-toad-looking thing
that crashed Chloe and Jimmy's wedding?

00:19.185 --> 00:21.767
-Kryptonian.
-Mm.

00:23.773 --> 00:26.560
And the spaceship that I found
in the woods near the dam.

00:27.277 --> 00:30.815
Also Kryptonian.
That wasn't mine. It was my cousin's.

00:32.490 --> 00:36.403
Sorry about the third degree. It's not
every week a girl learns her boyfriend's an—

00:36.578 --> 00:38.159
Alien?

00:38.830 --> 00:40.570
And you're still okay with that?

00:40.790 --> 00:41.950
LOIS:
Are you kidding me?

00:42.667 --> 00:47.331
It's like dating a god or Bono.

00:57.057 --> 01:00.049
At least we're on a story in the boonies,
and I get to play 20 questions...

01:00.226 --> 01:04.139
...without our nosy little kitty cat
snifﬁng around.

01:04.314 --> 01:07.852
It's lucky that Tess sent us out here
to cover the Cherry Festival.

01:09.360 --> 01:12.352
Clark Kent doesn't believe in luck.

01:13.239 --> 01:15.855
What'd you do, Clark?

01:20.371 --> 01:23.283
I didn't want you in the middle
of tonight's anti-hero protest.

01:23.458 --> 01:26.450
Clark, that should've been my story.
Why did you chop-block me?

01:26.628 --> 01:31.247
Your articles in support of the Blur
put you in the eye of the anti-hero storm.

01:31.424 --> 01:35.793
So you're gonna lock me in a castle tower
like I'm some damsel in distress?

01:35.970 --> 01:38.586
Lois, I just wanna make sure
that you're safe.

01:41.226 --> 01:47.438
Clark, I love that an intergalactic
powerhouse wants to protect me...

01:48.108 --> 01:51.191
...but this Earth girl
can take care of herself.

01:51.361 --> 01:53.101
[THUD]

02:07.919 --> 02:10.080
I don't even see what we hit.

02:11.005 --> 02:12.666
Two ﬂats and only one spare.

02:12.882 --> 02:14.793
Looks like a job for...

02:17.595 --> 02:20.302
And there's no reception.

02:22.267 --> 02:23.723
Want me to change that tire for you?

02:23.893 --> 02:24.928
[CLARK CHUCKLES]

02:25.103 --> 02:27.094
I think I can handle it.

02:29.065 --> 02:30.680
LOIS:
Wow.

02:40.743 --> 02:42.358
[CH UCKLES]

02:49.836 --> 02:51.622
Thank you.

02:53.006 --> 02:54.746
GIRL:
Oh, praise the Lord.

02:54.924 --> 02:57.085
You're okay.

02:57.760 --> 03:01.127
That's okay.
There's nothing a mechanic can't ﬁx.

03:01.764 --> 03:03.345
Do you know
where there's one nearby?

03:03.516 --> 03:07.008
-Um, up the road a bit, in Meeker Springs.
CLARK: Thanks.

03:07.270 --> 03:10.433
All right, Lois. Well, if we leave now,
we'll be back in a ﬂash.

03:10.815 --> 03:13.101
Oh, but, Clark,
I'm such a delicate ﬂower.

03:13.443 --> 03:17.356
I will-- I will wilt in that heat.

03:17.530 --> 03:20.112
-I think I'll just stay with, uh--
-Charlotte, ma'am.

03:20.283 --> 03:23.320
I got some fresh-squeezed lemonade,
if you like.

03:23.494 --> 03:28.238
Ah. Lovely. So we will have big glass as
we damsels in distress wait for Clark...

03:29.459 --> 03:30.790
...to come rescue us.

03:36.591 --> 03:38.627
Lois, is there a problem?

03:39.093 --> 03:43.678
Okay. First, it's not safe in the asphalt
jungle and now I'm at risk in Green Acres?

03:43.848 --> 03:45.349
We're in the middle of nowhere.

03:45.516 --> 03:48.883
Think horse-and-buggy girl will hurt me?
Is she gonna dimple me to death?

03:49.062 --> 03:50.268
CHARLOTTE:
Here you go.

03:51.981 --> 03:53.517
-Thank you, Charlotte.
-Mm-hm.

03:53.691 --> 03:57.149
Now, why don't we watch
while my knight in shining armor...

03:58.613 --> 04:00.319
...saves the day.

04:00.865 --> 04:02.696
It's gonna be a long walk, Lancelot...

04:02.867 --> 04:06.530
...but we will be right here waiting
for your triumphant return.

04:14.921 --> 04:16.502
Still watching.

04:36.859 --> 04:38.850
[CAR BEEPING]

04:46.828 --> 04:48.534
CLARK:
Lois?

04:51.541 --> 04:53.452
Lois?

05:46.596 --> 05:48.552
Lois?

05:52.268 --> 05:54.179
No service.

05:56.022 --> 05:57.637
[CAR APPROACHING]

05:57.815 --> 05:58.850
[GRUNTS]

05:59.025 --> 06:00.310
[CAR DOOR OPENS THEN CLOSES]

06:00.485 --> 06:02.146
Ah!

06:03.112 --> 06:05.023
ELLIS:
Something I can help you with?

06:07.575 --> 06:09.190
My girlfriend, she's missing.

06:09.369 --> 06:12.611
I went into town to get a ﬂat ﬁxed
and now she's gone.

06:12.789 --> 06:16.532
We were in an argument when I left,
I thought maybe she was mad at me...

06:16.709 --> 06:19.792
...but I can't ﬁnd her.
You know, I've searched everywhere.

06:19.962 --> 06:23.125
Better wrap that. Cut looks pretty nasty.

06:23.299 --> 06:25.585
How bad was your little argument?

06:26.135 --> 06:27.636
Well....

06:27.804 --> 06:30.716
No, this is from the rim of the tire.
That's where I cut it.

06:30.890 --> 06:33.006
There was a girl here. She might know.

06:33.184 --> 06:35.800
-Gir|?
-Charlotte. She was about 12 years old.

06:36.020 --> 06:39.308
She was selling produce.
She had a horse and buggy.

06:39.524 --> 06:42.891
We're in the middle of nowhere.
Never seen anybody set up shop here.

06:43.069 --> 06:44.400
There's not enough trafﬁc.

06:44.570 --> 06:47.186
I know what I saw, all right?
I'm not making this up.

06:47.365 --> 06:50.323
-Why don't we go to the station?
-Not going anywhere till Lois gets back.

06:50.493 --> 06:52.233
Mister, calm yourself down.

06:52.412 --> 06:53.652
Look.

06:55.581 --> 06:58.072
This must be what we ran over.

06:59.669 --> 07:02.661
If our blowout wasn't an accident,
someone could've done this on purpose.

07:02.839 --> 07:05.626
I think you better get a move on
before you get yourself in trouble.

07:05.800 --> 07:09.088
-Just trying to show you—
-l'm not gonna say it again.

07:14.684 --> 07:16.345
Those are tracks from the buggy.

07:16.519 --> 07:19.181
Now, if there was no girl,
how do you explain those?

07:19.355 --> 07:21.516
They do look fresh.

07:21.691 --> 07:24.023
Run up the logging road a bit.

07:24.193 --> 07:27.811
All right, you proved your point.
Let's take a hike.

07:27.989 --> 07:31.527
If your girlfriend is out there,
we'll ﬁnd her.

07:33.786 --> 07:35.162
CHARLOTTE:
Hyah.

07:35.329 --> 07:37.285
Captain, come on.

07:41.043 --> 07:42.499
Look at you drive that horse.

07:42.670 --> 07:45.503
At your age, the best I could do
was drive my dad crazy.

07:45.673 --> 07:48.085
Lucky for me you were around.

07:48.718 --> 07:52.836
How much longer before our carbon-free
hayride gets us to the train station?

07:53.014 --> 07:56.632
Oh, not much.
But I'm not allowed to go into town.

07:56.809 --> 07:58.891
My father will give you a ride
from here.

07:59.103 --> 08:02.561
LOIS: As long as I can make the express
back to cover the rally, I'm happy.

08:02.732 --> 08:07.192
I won't miss out on a story just because
he thinks I can't take care of myself.

08:09.572 --> 08:11.563
So your town is quaint.

08:11.741 --> 08:15.325
-How many people live out here?
-Our whole congregation.

08:15.870 --> 08:18.828
We're believers. Father bought this land
long before I was born...

08:18.998 --> 08:22.866
...and moved his ﬂock here from Idaho
so we could all live together.

08:30.760 --> 08:32.250
CHARLOTTE:
Whoa.

08:36.766 --> 08:38.927
Looks like you're having
some sort of shindig.

08:39.143 --> 08:40.679
It's the harvest festival.

08:40.853 --> 08:42.889
Whole town comes out to celebrate.

08:43.397 --> 08:45.012
Bless us, child.

08:45.191 --> 08:47.603
How'd you bring a guest
to our home unannounced...

08:47.777 --> 08:50.234
...when we're unprepared
to welcome them? I'm Ruth.

08:50.404 --> 08:52.190
Ruth Cavanaugh.

08:52.365 --> 08:53.445
Lois Lane.

08:53.658 --> 08:56.900
Miss Lane just needs Father
to give her a ride to the train station...

08:57.078 --> 08:59.615
...so she can get back to the city.

08:59.789 --> 09:02.121
I don't mean to impose,
Charlotte just offered.

09:02.291 --> 09:05.454
Never an imposition
to help those in need.

09:05.670 --> 09:08.582
But my husband likes his supper
promptly at sundown.

09:09.090 --> 09:11.877
He'll take you right after we eat.

09:12.468 --> 09:16.131
You know, if you point the way,
I'm sure I could just hoof it from here.

09:16.305 --> 09:17.385
Don't be foolish.

09:17.557 --> 09:21.141
If you're not familiar with these parts,
you could get lost in those woods.

09:21.310 --> 09:24.143
Stay. Break bread with us.

09:24.313 --> 09:26.599
Mother always makes more than enough.

09:29.402 --> 09:31.643
Rally's not for another couple of hours.

09:34.156 --> 09:36.693
And I could really use
a home-cooked meal.

09:37.076 --> 09:39.613
Good, good.

09:39.787 --> 09:43.655
Go fetch your father, Charlotte,
tell him the ham needs carving.

09:43.833 --> 09:45.323
This way.

09:47.628 --> 09:49.744
MR. CAVANAUGH:
Good. That's nice.

09:52.758 --> 09:55.249
Did you see her, Father?

09:56.846 --> 10:01.215
Good work, child. You've saved us all.

10:04.520 --> 10:07.432
KIDS:
Happy birthday, Alexander.

10:07.607 --> 10:09.347
[CHEERING]

10:23.706 --> 10:26.698
-Happy birthday.
KIDS: Happy birthday, Alexander.

10:26.876 --> 10:28.366
Happy birthday.

10:28.544 --> 10:30.330
[KIDS CHATTERING AND LAUGHING]

10:31.881 --> 10:34.543
Thank you. This is the best party ever.

10:34.717 --> 10:36.002
You're welcome.

10:36.177 --> 10:37.758
[DOOR OPENS]

10:38.679 --> 10:42.513
I have work to do, so make sure you
save me a really big piece of cake, okay?

10:42.683 --> 10:43.763
-Okay.
-Okay.

10:59.075 --> 11:01.817
My team is still searching
for a remedy...

11:01.994 --> 11:04.155
...but I don't wanna make
any false promises.

11:10.586 --> 11:13.419
All our tests indicate
that his condition is irreversible.

11:13.923 --> 11:17.882
If the accelerated mitosis persists,
his body will eventually give out.

11:18.052 --> 11:19.087
I'm very sorry.

11:19.303 --> 11:23.091
He's aged four years in two weeks,
so sorry isn't good enough.

11:27.520 --> 11:30.512
He needs to be at the facility
where we can study him.

11:30.690 --> 11:33.022
Alexander stays here with me.

11:38.698 --> 11:41.064
I want him to believe
he is like any other child.

11:41.242 --> 11:43.449
But we both know he's not normal.

11:43.953 --> 11:47.571
And no matter how many parties
you throw him, he never will be.

11:51.335 --> 11:53.792
I just wanna protect him.

11:55.715 --> 11:57.546
I wanna give him a second chance.

12:00.136 --> 12:02.593
Dr. Lamell, I know
that you had a hand...

12:02.763 --> 12:06.301
...in the horrors that Lex Luthor committed
in his labs over the years.

12:09.979 --> 12:12.140
And I chose you to run this team...

12:12.356 --> 12:15.143
...because I know
deep down in your heart...

12:15.401 --> 12:17.232
...you wanna make things right.

12:19.655 --> 12:21.566
-More than anything.
-Okay.

12:26.662 --> 12:30.496
You ﬁnd me a cure to save Alexander
and I promise you...

12:30.666 --> 12:33.658
...I will not let him become that monster.

12:35.171 --> 12:36.411
[THUDDING AND KIDS SHRIEKING]

12:36.589 --> 12:38.580
GIRL 1:
Help! Help! Someone come quick.

12:38.758 --> 12:40.999
GIRL 2: Oh, my God.
-A|exander.

12:44.972 --> 12:47.509
Do something. Help him.

13:10.831 --> 13:12.207
CLARK:
Lois?

13:12.374 --> 13:13.454
Lois.

13:13.626 --> 13:15.867
ELLIS: Mister, I think we're barking up
the wrong tree.

13:16.045 --> 13:18.832
There's nothing out here for miles.

13:19.381 --> 13:21.372
These tracks are probably left
by hunters.

13:21.550 --> 13:24.041
They bring in carts
to haul out game all the time.

13:24.220 --> 13:27.337
Do they also leave spikes in the road
to give people ﬂat tires?

13:27.515 --> 13:30.552
Two-by-four probably fell off
a passing truck.

13:30.726 --> 13:34.560
Look, it's only natural for you
to be worried about your girlfriend.

13:35.731 --> 13:39.064
-She's the most important thing in my life.
-You said she was upset with you.

13:39.235 --> 13:41.191
I bet she hitched a ride.

13:41.362 --> 13:45.025
You go back to Metropolis
and I guarantee she'll be waiting.

13:49.245 --> 13:51.156
-There are crystals in this water?
-Ah.

13:51.956 --> 13:55.369
Meteor shower of '89.
A couple of meteors hit the spring.

13:55.543 --> 13:57.249
-Blue meteor rock?
-Yeah.

13:57.419 --> 13:59.580
Killed one local
and destroyed acres of crops.

13:59.755 --> 14:01.586
But it did give us a gift.

14:06.595 --> 14:08.426
Best drinking water in the county.

14:08.597 --> 14:09.928
Meteor seems to purify it.

14:10.099 --> 14:12.010
And everyone here is okay?

14:12.184 --> 14:14.596
Because I grew up in Smallville.

14:14.895 --> 14:17.932
The green meteor rock has been harming
people for the last 20 years.

14:18.107 --> 14:20.018
Not here.
Been drinking this water my whole life.

14:20.192 --> 14:22.774
I haven't had so much
as a common cold. Ha, ha.

14:22.945 --> 14:24.776
Yep, we're all just ﬁne.

14:24.947 --> 14:26.687
[BELL RINGING IN DISTANCE]

14:27.533 --> 14:29.489
If there's nothing out here,
what was that?

14:29.660 --> 14:32.117
Something I wish you hadn't heard.

14:46.010 --> 14:48.126
I'm sorry I ruined the party.

14:48.304 --> 14:50.420
It's not your fault.

14:50.598 --> 14:53.055
I know that something's wrong with me.
I'm a freak.

14:53.225 --> 14:56.217
No. No, you're not.
You're a beautiful little boy...

14:56.395 --> 15:00.388
...and I promise you that I am going
to make everything okay.

15:01.317 --> 15:02.932
Okay?

15:05.237 --> 15:07.819
You have to tell me something.

15:08.574 --> 15:11.441
Right before you blacked out,
you were drawing this.

15:12.953 --> 15:14.659
How do you know this symbol?

15:15.039 --> 15:18.156
It-- It's just a drawing.

15:19.627 --> 15:21.618
Alexander...

15:22.671 --> 15:26.084
...I found these hidden in your closet.

15:32.348 --> 15:34.304
Please tell me what they mean to you.

15:35.434 --> 15:38.176
It's the symbol of the bad man.

15:38.687 --> 15:42.179
He comes into my dreams to hurt me.

15:43.943 --> 15:45.683
I'd never let anyone hurt you.

15:45.861 --> 15:48.819
-You can't stop him.
-You're safe here.

15:48.989 --> 15:52.026
No, he's the strongest man
in the whole world.

15:52.201 --> 15:55.944
-You can't protect me.
-l'd never let anything happen to you.

15:56.121 --> 15:58.498
He wants to kill me!

16:11.387 --> 16:15.346
I know this is hard for you to believe
when you're so frightened, but....

16:16.225 --> 16:18.056
Alexander, I'm here for you.

16:26.151 --> 16:28.107
Alexander?

16:32.616 --> 16:34.652
Alexander?

16:35.828 --> 16:38.035
Alexander.

16:47.923 --> 16:49.834
Yummy.

16:50.009 --> 16:54.628
And to think you ﬁxed this all
without a KitchenAid or Costco.

16:59.643 --> 17:01.850
We believe in living a simple life.

17:02.021 --> 17:06.014
No modern technology
and no worldly temptation.

17:06.900 --> 17:08.765
We keep to ourselves.

17:09.194 --> 17:12.277
Helps us stay on the righteous path.

17:12.448 --> 17:14.780
Uh, speaking of paths...

17:14.950 --> 17:17.282
...isn't it time we hit the road?

17:18.454 --> 17:21.912
Our teachings say
when people come together to eat...

17:22.082 --> 17:23.913
...you make time for your fellow man.

17:24.418 --> 17:28.627
Trust me, you don't forget
Sunday school on the military base.

17:28.797 --> 17:30.879
You should ﬁnish your dinner.

17:33.469 --> 17:36.552
It would be bad luck
for a guest to leave our table early...

17:36.722 --> 17:38.804
...on the night
of the harvest celebration.

17:38.974 --> 17:42.637
Yeah, as long as we hit the road
as soon as we're ﬁnished.

17:46.398 --> 17:50.437
I would love to stay
and see the festivities one day.

17:51.236 --> 17:53.318
Bet that's a lot of fun.

17:53.489 --> 17:56.071
MR. CAVANAUGH:
Fun has nothing to do with it.

17:56.575 --> 17:59.487
We glorify the day we were shown
the Lord's sign.

18:02.331 --> 18:05.448
What exactly was the sign?

18:11.965 --> 18:14.752
The ﬁre came from the heavens...

18:14.968 --> 18:17.345
...tear down our village.

18:17.513 --> 18:21.176
And our daughter, Esther,
was taken from us.

18:25.020 --> 18:31.516
She was ringing the town bell
to warn everyone of the danger.

18:31.693 --> 18:34.435
She was struck down where she stood.

18:34.863 --> 18:37.730
Oh, I am so sorry.

18:38.158 --> 18:39.694
That's awful.

18:41.662 --> 18:44.779
MR. CAVANAUGH: Before that,
we suffered terrible drought...

18:44.957 --> 18:47.699
...and years of bad crops.

18:48.001 --> 18:50.617
People were hungry and sick.

18:52.756 --> 18:55.839
But our daughter gave her life
so that we could all prosper.

18:57.344 --> 19:04.011
Ever since, our crops have been bountiful
and our people never get sick.

19:04.560 --> 19:06.471
Amen.

19:08.647 --> 19:12.014
And you think this happened
because your daughter died?

19:17.406 --> 19:21.649
I'm pretty sure that didn't make it
into the Good Book I read.

19:24.371 --> 19:27.534
I don't expect you to understand.

19:27.708 --> 19:29.039
You're not a believer.

19:30.586 --> 19:36.923
But every year, since her death,
we have offered our Lord a sacriﬁce...

19:38.218 --> 19:40.675
...and he has rewarded us.

19:50.230 --> 19:55.600
-If you're done, I'll clear your plate.
-Oh, yeah. Stuffed.

19:56.069 --> 19:57.445
Thank you.

19:57.613 --> 19:59.569
It was lovely.

20:03.869 --> 20:05.109
Psst. Charlotte.

20:05.287 --> 20:09.200
I'm a little squeamish when it comes
to the slaughtering of the fatted calf...

20:09.374 --> 20:11.956
...so just tell your parents thank you,
okay?

20:12.127 --> 20:14.083
I'm
