20:14.713 --> 20:16.544
We'll never let you leave.

20:17.758 --> 20:20.795
-What?
-You've been chosen.

20:20.969 --> 20:23.381
Just like my sister.

20:25.057 --> 20:27.264
This was your last supper.

20:32.648 --> 20:33.683
WOMAN:
There she is.

20:37.069 --> 20:39.060
[GRUNTING]

20:41.073 --> 20:42.984
[LOIS PANTING]

20:43.784 --> 20:45.149
MR. CAVANAUGH:
Rejoice, my people.

20:45.953 --> 20:47.909
We have our sacriﬁce.

20:48.080 --> 20:51.288
ALL:
Praise the Lord!

20:55.254 --> 20:57.961
LOIS:
What is wrong with you people?

21:02.469 --> 21:03.925
LOIS:
Clark.

21:04.346 --> 21:05.552
Clark, wake up.

21:09.226 --> 21:10.932
Lois.

21:14.856 --> 21:16.312
What happened to you?

21:16.483 --> 21:19.316
I really stepped in it. I was steamed
you kept me from that rally scoop.

21:19.486 --> 21:21.522
I ended up trapping us
in the Village of the Damned.

21:21.697 --> 21:24.985
I've been looking for you for hours.
I'm just glad you're okay.

21:25.534 --> 21:29.527
Won't be for long. These holy rollers
from hell wanna make me a sacriﬁce...

21:29.705 --> 21:32.071
...so they can grow bigger tomatoes.

21:33.667 --> 21:36.079
I promise to eat a helping of crow
when we get home.

21:36.378 --> 21:38.710
But right now,
do your super-speedy thing...

21:38.880 --> 21:42.293
...because this fair lady needs
some rescuing, big time.

21:44.386 --> 21:46.092
I can't.

21:46.263 --> 21:49.175
Clark, now is not the time for jokes.

21:49.391 --> 21:53.760
The water is contaminated with blue meteor.
They've been drinking it for years.

21:53.937 --> 21:56.895
Maybe that's what makes them so healthy,
not to mention wackadoodle.

21:57.065 --> 22:00.899
It's infected their bodies. When I'm
around them, I don't have my abilities.

22:01.069 --> 22:04.903
I've got to get far enough away from
them so my powers can come back.

22:05.073 --> 22:06.938
Meteor rock.

22:07.117 --> 22:11.656
Maybe that's why when I pulled that
blue dagger out of you, you healed.

22:12.414 --> 22:13.654
You did that?

22:15.292 --> 22:16.407
Yeah.

22:17.085 --> 22:20.543
Lois, you didn'tjust heal me,
you brought me back.

22:20.964 --> 22:22.295
You saved me.

22:22.924 --> 22:24.334
Well...

22:24.509 --> 22:27.251
...sometimes even a hero needs
a guardian angel, Clark.

22:29.056 --> 22:32.765
I wish you had wings that could ﬂy us out.
The house seems to be surrounded.

22:32.934 --> 22:36.426
Our best chance is for me to get past
the guards before they ﬁre a shot.

22:36.605 --> 22:39.312
I hate to burst your bubble,
but without your powers...

22:39.483 --> 22:41.644
...you won't be able to outrun
their speeding bullets.

22:41.818 --> 22:43.683
[FLOORBOARD CREAKING]

22:45.364 --> 22:47.480
But maybe there's another way
out of Dodge.

22:49.534 --> 22:51.149
Clark.

22:53.705 --> 22:56.617
If this leads to a cellar,
there might be a way out of here.

23:04.257 --> 23:05.793
Clark.

23:08.053 --> 23:09.338
[CLARK GRUNTS]

23:09.763 --> 23:10.843
I can't.

23:17.145 --> 23:20.854
Whenever the general grounded me,
I always found a way to escape.

23:21.024 --> 23:24.016
This Army brat has picked more locks
than Harry Houdini.

23:30.409 --> 23:34.652
Change your clothes or you're gonna
stick out like a stripper in a seminary.

23:45.507 --> 23:49.546
Why are we never someplace romantic
when he takes off his shirt?

23:56.435 --> 24:00.019
Thank you for locating him.
I'll take it from here.

24:09.573 --> 24:13.065
-A|exander.
-This barn is just like I remember.

24:15.537 --> 24:18.529
But you've never been here before.

24:19.207 --> 24:20.663
Yes, I have.

24:20.834 --> 24:24.418
Do you see his bow tie?
It was the ﬁrst one he ever wore.

24:24.588 --> 24:27.330
And I tied it for him, here.

24:29.718 --> 24:32.926
-That was probably just a dream.
-No, it was real.

24:33.096 --> 24:35.758
Right here, he told me
that we'd be friends forever...

24:35.932 --> 24:40.847
...that he wanted to be my brother.
And at the window...

24:42.814 --> 24:46.557
...I told him that our friendship
would be the thing of legend.

24:47.277 --> 24:49.768
Alexander, if that's what you want...

24:50.322 --> 24:52.563
...you have a chance
to make that happen.

24:55.660 --> 24:59.278
How can I ever trust Clark again?
He made my father hate me.

24:59.456 --> 25:01.822
He took away everything
that I ever cared about.

25:02.000 --> 25:03.661
And the last time I was up here...

25:03.835 --> 25:06.577
...I begged him to tell me the truth
about himself.

25:06.755 --> 25:09.167
But as always,
he denied who he really was.

25:09.341 --> 25:12.799
Clark is not the bad man, Alexander.

25:12.969 --> 25:14.925
Lex is.

25:15.180 --> 25:18.138
He used you just like he used me.

25:18.308 --> 25:21.095
And you don't deserve what's happened.

25:21.811 --> 25:24.848
You don't have to buy into his memories.

25:26.316 --> 25:27.396
I will help you.

25:27.609 --> 25:30.066
Why?
So you can feel good about yourself?

25:30.237 --> 25:33.354
So you can exorcise those demons
deep within your soul?

25:34.449 --> 25:35.985
Isn't that what you've always wanted?

25:36.159 --> 25:39.526
To save the world
so you could redeem the evil inside you.

25:39.704 --> 25:40.989
Stop it.

25:41.164 --> 25:43.906
But you couldn't do it alone,
so you clung to powerful men.

25:44.125 --> 25:45.626
Enough.

25:45.794 --> 25:48.285
First Oliver Queen, then me...

25:48.463 --> 25:51.626
...then Zod. And now, Clark Kent.

25:55.262 --> 25:57.218
I'm so sorry.
I shouldn't have done that.

25:57.389 --> 26:01.177
I just wanna help you. I know that
I can do this. I know that I can save you.

26:01.351 --> 26:05.685
How can you save me when there's
so much you don't know about yourself?

26:06.147 --> 26:07.557
Please.

26:07.857 --> 26:09.643
Please.

26:10.527 --> 26:12.984
-Alexander—
-Don't call me that.

26:13.154 --> 26:15.236
My name is Lex.

26:19.703 --> 26:21.659
[MURMURING]

26:40.181 --> 26:42.012
SANDRA:
Sister.

26:42.684 --> 26:45.300
You don't have ﬂowers
for the celebration.

26:49.232 --> 26:51.188
Thank you, sister.

26:55.697 --> 26:56.903
It's you.

26:57.532 --> 27:00.865
Well, I guess you can't get the city
out of this country girl, huh?

27:01.036 --> 27:02.697
-Let's go.
WOMAN: Are you all right?

27:03.204 --> 27:06.196
Don't let them get away!

27:08.710 --> 27:11.201
Stop them! Stop them!

27:12.547 --> 27:14.003
[HORSE NEIGHS]

27:17.969 --> 27:19.550
MAN 1: Hold them. Hold her.
LOIS: Clark.

27:19.721 --> 27:21.928
CLARK: No.
LOIS: Hey.

27:32.942 --> 27:36.025
-You will be offered up tonight.
-I won't let you hurt her.

27:36.237 --> 27:37.397
You're a mere mortal...

27:38.239 --> 27:40.696
...and you will not defy
the will of our Lord!

27:40.867 --> 27:42.403
[GRUNTS]

27:44.496 --> 27:45.827
LOIS:
Clark.

27:46.247 --> 27:49.284
No! Clark. Clark!

27:49.918 --> 27:51.954
Clark! Clark!

27:53.088 --> 27:54.498
No! Clark!

27:54.673 --> 27:57.255
No. No!

28:19.489 --> 28:21.275
You didn't have to kill him.

28:21.449 --> 28:23.280
He would have told others about us.

28:25.412 --> 28:29.246
No one can keep us from our holy task.

28:31.084 --> 28:35.373
Our Lord has shown us the light.

28:37.298 --> 28:38.959
The light?

28:40.427 --> 28:45.797
You justify this by calling it a sacriﬁce,
but you know it's murder.

28:45.974 --> 28:48.465
Whatever happened to
"Thou shalt not kill"?

28:49.144 --> 28:52.682
We follow his example.

28:53.648 --> 28:55.479
Every year, for 20 years...

28:56.443 --> 29:02.279
...a young woman has been sacriﬁced
with ﬁre from above, just like Esther.

29:02.449 --> 29:08.115
And for that, our Lord has rewarded
his devoted ﬂock.

29:10.498 --> 29:13.831
My daughter was the ﬁrst to give her life.

29:14.210 --> 29:16.121
You won't be the last.

29:18.339 --> 29:21.547
I can't imagine the pain
you must have suffered...

29:21.718 --> 29:24.175
...when you lost Esther.

29:25.054 --> 29:27.545
But killing all of those women
in her name was wrong.

29:27.724 --> 29:30.557
She would be ashamed
of how you've lead your people astray.

29:30.727 --> 29:31.967
Silence!

29:33.521 --> 29:35.853
You do not understand...

29:36.024 --> 29:37.810
...because...

29:38.026 --> 29:41.018
-...you do not have faith.
-I have faith.

29:45.033 --> 29:46.239
I have faith.

29:48.870 --> 29:55.036
Faith has nothing to do with blindly
following this misguided messiah.

29:55.210 --> 29:59.670
I believe in knowing right from wrong,
just like you all do.

30:02.509 --> 30:04.670
Deep down, you know this isn't right.

30:04.844 --> 30:06.709
She does not know what we suffered...

30:06.888 --> 30:10.221
...before his ﬁery wrath rained down
from the heavens.

30:11.226 --> 30:13.763
But you remember those dark days.

30:13.978 --> 30:16.264
If we let her live...

30:16.481 --> 30:19.393
...a vengeful God will smite us yet again.

30:19.567 --> 30:21.398
And mark my words...

30:21.903 --> 30:23.734
...this time...

30:23.905 --> 30:26.863
...he will take one of your daughters.

30:27.492 --> 30:31.531
Ben, would you give up your daughter,
Sarah?

30:33.915 --> 30:35.280
Any of you?

30:37.418 --> 30:42.037
I say,
better to sacriﬁce a nonbeliever...

30:43.091 --> 30:45.924
...than to lose another one of our own.

30:55.270 --> 30:58.103
You don't have to do this.

30:58.815 --> 31:00.976
-This won't bring her back.
-Shh.

31:01.150 --> 31:02.811
It won't.

31:03.778 --> 31:05.109
God forgives you.

31:08.783 --> 31:11.115
SANDRA: You think he was still alive
when we buried him?

31:11.286 --> 31:16.121
If he was, he's dead now.
Forced our hand.

31:16.291 --> 31:19.283
Should've listened to me and headed back
to the city when he had the chance.

31:19.460 --> 31:20.540
TOWNSPEOPLE:
Praise the Lord!

31:20.712 --> 31:22.998
Come on now,
the ceremony's about to begin.

31:23.172 --> 31:27.040
MR. CAVANAUGH:
He takes vengeance on his adversaries.

31:40.773 --> 31:43.856
TOWNSPEOPLE:
Glory be to the Lord.

31:44.068 --> 31:45.808
Amen.

31:51.200 --> 31:52.656
Let us pray.

31:53.161 --> 31:58.997
Dear Lord, accept this offering
as our complete devotion to you.

31:59.167 --> 32:04.662
Take her, so that your people may see
another harvest of bountiful crops...

32:06.007 --> 32:08.168
...and another year without sickness.

32:08.343 --> 32:09.958
TOWNSPEOPLE:
Praise the Lord.

32:10.136 --> 32:12.878
MAN 1: Praise the Lord.
MAN 2: Praise the Lord.

32:22.398 --> 32:24.013
[GUNSHOT]

32:26.527 --> 32:28.518
Get away from her.

32:28.863 --> 32:30.194
Clark.

32:34.243 --> 32:37.235
No, she must be sacriﬁced.

32:48.883 --> 32:51.545
[YELLS]

33:03.731 --> 33:04.937
This is a trick.

33:05.149 --> 33:06.730
Clark.

33:10.279 --> 33:12.895
-C|ark.
-Look what he's been through, Joshua...

33:13.074 --> 33:15.565
...and he's still alive. It's a sign.

33:15.743 --> 33:17.529
MAN:
It's a sign.

33:24.043 --> 33:25.419
Yes, it's a sign.

33:26.587 --> 33:28.043
Move back.

33:32.218 --> 33:34.880
You are not worthy
to be in his presence.

33:39.267 --> 33:43.761
Drop your weapon
and beg for forgiveness.

33:44.981 --> 33:46.892
No, I don't think you get it.

33:47.817 --> 33:51.184
He is a messenger sent from the heavens.

33:53.781 --> 33:54.987
I don't believe you.

33:57.452 --> 33:58.658
Lois.

33:58.828 --> 34:00.614
Oh, you better believe it.

34:00.788 --> 34:02.779
Because if you don't listen...

34:02.957 --> 34:06.825
...he will strike down upon thee...

34:07.003 --> 34:10.211
...with great vengeance
and furious anger.

34:11.215 --> 34:16.755
And he will use his heat vision
to raze your village...

34:17.263 --> 34:19.970
...and his super-breath
to smite your crops!

34:20.475 --> 34:21.590
Amen.

34:23.436 --> 34:28.146
What do you say you speed us away
from these Children of the Corn, honey?

34:55.676 --> 34:58.509
Is this all that you were able to make?

35:00.348 --> 35:02.304
Considering we just found the research...

35:02.475 --> 35:06.514
...we were only able to synthesize
a small amount, but it's a start.

35:08.689 --> 35:11.647
You said Alexander's condition
was irreversible.

35:11.818 --> 35:13.809
That's what we believed.

35:14.570 --> 35:17.482
But on your advice, we scoured
the LuthorCorp database...

35:17.657 --> 35:19.943
...and came across
Peter Dinsmore's work.

35:20.159 --> 35:23.196
He's the architect of Lionel Luthor's
genetic engineering program.

35:23.371 --> 35:25.362
He cloned his own daughter...

35:25.540 --> 35:29.954
...and encountered the same
accelerated mitosis complication.

35:30.378 --> 35:33.745
But I was able to use his research
and formulate that serum.

35:33.965 --> 35:35.250
A cure...

35:35.883 --> 35:37.168
...to save Alexander.

35:37.510 --> 35:39.341
It's the breakthrough we wanted.

35:49.564 --> 35:53.523
This could be the redemption
we both have been praying for.

36:00.741 --> 36:03.232
I wanted so badly...

36:03.411 --> 36:05.242
...to save that little boy.

36:15.631 --> 36:18.543
Miss Mercer, what are you doing?

36:19.218 --> 36:21.504
Destroy all of your research.

36:22.221 --> 36:26.260
And in the morning,
he'll be locked up again...

36:26.434 --> 36:28.641
...for everyone's safety.

36:28.811 --> 36:31.598
If we don't begin his therapy,
he'll be dead in six weeks.

36:31.772 --> 36:33.433
That's the point.

36:33.900 --> 36:36.437
Because he's notjust a clone.

36:37.028 --> 36:38.814
He is Lex Luthor.

36:50.917 --> 36:54.125
It seems our Stephen King's romp
in the backwoods...

36:54.295 --> 36:58.789
...bumped Cat Grant's anti-hero crusade
from column one.

37:00.968 --> 37:05.632
Leave it to Lois and Clark to turn a quiet
day in the country into a major scoop.

37:05.806 --> 37:09.014
Friends at the bureau said our
Koresh wannabes were so low proﬁle...

37:09.185 --> 37:10.846
...they weren't on anybody's radar.

37:11.062 --> 37:14.475
I just wish we'd found them sooner.
We could've saved so many lives.

37:16.817 --> 37:19.103
I don't understand
how believers would allow themselves...

37:19.278 --> 37:21.655
...to be led down such a dark path.

37:24.367 --> 37:26.358
I guess there's so much chaos
out there...

37:26.577 --> 37:31.196
...people are just desperate
for something to give them hope.

37:31.374 --> 37:36.084
Now more than ever,
the world needs someone to believe in.

37:36.879 --> 37:40.838
-I think I know where this is going.
-Hear me out, Clark.

37:41.008 --> 37:43.841
Hey, I wasn't a big fan
of Ollie's coming-out party...

37:44.303 --> 37:48.137
...and I used to think that it was best
for you to stay in the shadows too...

37:49.308 --> 37:53.847
...but maybe, someday soon,
you'll have to step into the light.

37:54.855 --> 37:59.519
You could be a symbol to inspire everyone
that this planet could be a better place.

37:59.860 --> 38:03.193
I'm not sure anyone is ready to believe
in a stranger from a strange land.

38:03.364 --> 38:04.729
Hmm.

38:04.907 --> 38:07.740
If they know the real Clark Kent...

38:07.910 --> 38:12.654
...then I am sure the rest of the world
will believe in you as much as I do.

38:14.625 --> 38:18.243
I'm sorry I was so overprotective.
I was trying to keep you safe.

38:18.421 --> 38:20.537
If it wasn't for you...

38:20.715 --> 38:23.422
...I would be a crispy critter in Hellsville.

38:23.634 --> 38:26.376
No. You held your own...

38:27.388 --> 38:29.219
...even when I didn't have my powers.

38:30.391 --> 38:32.256
Lois, you saved my life.

38:33.060 --> 38:35.893
Guess there's enough danger out there
for everyone.

38:37.023 --> 38:40.231
We just have to trust that we'll always
be there for each other...

38:40.401 --> 38:42.562
...when times get tough.

38:50.911 --> 38:53.243
Which is why I want you to have this.

38:54.165 --> 38:55.780
LOIS:
Uh....

39:01.172 --> 39:04.084
The unabridged user's guide
to all things Kryptonian?

39:04.800 --> 39:07.257
It may ﬁll in a few blanks.

39:12.767 --> 39:15.383
I want you to know me completely,
with no secrets.

39:18.981 --> 39:20.937
Because you're the one...

39:21.609 --> 39:23.600
...you always will be.

42:19.286 --> 42:21.277
[English - US - SDH]
